01:45:38,910 --> 01:45:39,830
No!

1535
01:45:42,530 --> 01:45:44,370
Here it comes on you, Mini!

1536
01:45:51,120 --> 01:45:52,120
Rahul.

1537
01:45:53,630 --> 01:45:56,620
- Did you get your admission?
- Yes.

1538
01:45:58,070 --> 01:46:00,030
- So you'll go away?
- Yes.

1539
01:46:17,780 --> 01:46:18,880
Indu?

1540
01:46:19,710 --> 01:46:20,660
(Sighs)

1541
01:46:21,580 --> 01:46:22,740
Chanda?

1542
01:46:25,280 --> 01:46:26,440
What happened?

1543
01:46:31,270 --> 01:46:36,110
Major and I have once again...

1544
01:46:42,120 --> 01:46:44,340
You've understood what
I am trying to say, right?

1545
01:46:45,890 --> 01:46:46,580
Yes.

1546
01:46:46,660 --> 01:46:47,540
(Sighs)

1547
01:46:47,750 --> 01:46:50,890
Oh, Indu, this is the
happiest day of my life!

1548
01:46:51,340 --> 01:46:52,210
(Gasps)

1549
01:46:53,070 --> 01:46:57,190
But you would always say
that you don't need any support.

1550
01:46:57,790 --> 01:46:59,440
That you don't need a family.

1551
01:47:00,250 --> 01:47:02,760
And that you are an independent woman.

1552
01:47:03,650 --> 01:47:05,320
I know, Indu. I know.

1553
01:47:06,970 --> 01:47:08,830
It would be fine if I were just a woman.

1554
01:47:10,560 --> 01:47:11,780
But I'm a mother too.

1555
01:47:13,980 --> 01:47:16,120
When my child held my hand and said...

1556
01:47:16,780 --> 01:47:18,080
"Please come home, mummy"

1557
01:47:18,980 --> 01:47:20,190
...I couldn't hold myself back.

1558
01:47:22,020 --> 01:47:23,650
l just couldn't hold myself back, Indu.

1559
01:47:29,990 --> 01:47:31,320
Shall I say something, Indu?

1560
01:47:32,140 --> 01:47:35,820
A woman has no say when the
motherly feelings in her arise.

1561
01:47:36,780 --> 01:47:39,680
(Background music)

1562
01:47:40,080 --> 01:47:42,280
Mummy.

1563
01:47:42,390 --> 01:47:43,550
- Mummy!
- Hey!

1564
01:47:43,710 --> 01:47:46,790
- Hello, aunty.
- Hello.

1565
01:47:46,870 --> 01:47:48,390
- You tell her!
- You tell!

1566
01:47:48,410 --> 01:47:51,370
- What happened?
- Sister has stood first in class.

1567
01:47:51,430 --> 01:47:53,600
She defeated that fatso!

1568
01:47:54,110 --> 01:47:55,340
Very good! Well-done!

1569
01:47:55,580 --> 01:47:59,060
If Brother Rahul had not taught
her, it would've been impossible.

1570
01:47:59,410 --> 01:48:01,300
- Who's Rahul?
- Brother Rahul!

1571
01:48:02,100 --> 01:48:04,730
The boy whom I spoke to you about.

1572
01:48:06,080 --> 01:48:08,620
It's good that the kids have
mingled with each other so well.

1573
01:48:11,760 --> 01:48:13,390
Anita just look in that yellow file.

1574
01:48:20,790 --> 01:48:25,590
It's not in this either.
They are my personal papers!

1575
01:48:25,610 --> 01:48:27,950
They are Rahul's Nainital papers.
Where are they?

1576
01:48:28,360 --> 01:48:30,580
I had told you to keep them
in a personal file!

1577
01:48:30,870 --> 01:48:31,780
So, just look for them!

1578
01:48:31,830 --> 01:48:33,240
I have to send them
with Rahul to Nainital.

1579
01:48:33,670 --> 01:48:35,710
Look in that drawer, the lower one.

1580
01:48:36,450 --> 01:48:39,280
(Typewritter sound)

1581
01:48:42,060 --> 01:48:44,860
SECRETARY: Sir, are these the papers?

1582
01:48:46,470 --> 01:48:49,590
Yes. Where were they? Can't you
even file them properly?

1583
01:48:49,980 --> 01:48:50,730
Thanks.

1584
01:48:51,030 --> 01:48:54,030
- Rahul, take care of these.
- All right, uncle.

1585
01:48:54,110 --> 01:48:56,040
They are your papers.
Take them home.

1586
01:48:56,600 --> 01:48:58,520
- Are you being naughty?
- No.

1587
01:48:58,650 --> 01:49:00,210
Sit in my cabin.

1588
01:49:01,520 --> 01:49:03,080
I'll go meet Mr. Dhawan.

1589
01:49:14,600 --> 01:49:15,900
Hello.

1590
01:49:19,920 --> 01:49:22,490
(Typewriter sound)

1591
01:49:24,380 --> 01:49:25,190
Son.

1592
01:49:26,470 --> 01:49:29,390
This letter must have fallen
from those papers. Keep it there.

1593
01:49:29,860 --> 01:49:32,020
- Whose letter is it?
- To Mr. Malhotra...

1594
01:49:32,230 --> 01:49:34,400
from Gurudayal Singh, Nainital.

1595
01:49:34,430 --> 01:49:35,390
Give it to me.

1596
01:49:41,410 --> 01:49:44,340
(Background music)

1597
01:49:56,710 --> 01:49:57,670
Oh, I see.

1598
01:49:57,980 --> 01:49:58,940
I see.

1599
01:49:59,830 --> 01:50:03,190
You wanted a proposal from the
best architect. It had to be good.

1600
01:50:03,470 --> 01:50:04,890
I think we'll clinch the deal.

1601
01:50:05,660 --> 01:50:08,120
Yes... All right,
I'll call you tomorrow.

1602
01:50:08,960 --> 01:50:11,840
Fine... after 2-3 days.
Bye, Mr. Bansal. Thank you.

1603
01:50:12,690 --> 01:50:15,790
DK, I think Mr. Bansal has
liked your proposal very much.

1604
01:50:16,080 --> 01:50:18,430
DK I'm certain our conversation with him,

1605
01:50:18,480 --> 01:50:20,160
- that this contract is...
- That's great, sir.

1606
01:50:20,200 --> 01:50:22,240
Now, what we got to ensure is
when the first presentation...

1607
01:50:22,270 --> 01:50:23,280
Sir, excuse me. One minute.

1608
01:50:25,190 --> 01:50:26,070
Come on.

1609
01:50:29,720 --> 01:50:30,860
Come on!

1610
01:50:31,720 --> 01:50:32,880
Don't forget the papers.

1611
01:50:36,580 --> 01:50:38,070
That's... come on!

1612
01:50:46,660 --> 01:50:48,000
Who's this smart boy, DK?

1613
01:50:48,360 --> 01:50:50,000
This is... Rahul, sir.

1614
01:50:50,980 --> 01:50:52,150
Wish him, Rahul.

1615
01:50:52,930 --> 01:50:54,170
Wish him.

1616
01:50:54,340 --> 01:50:55,320
Hello, son!

1617
01:50:55,860 --> 01:50:58,380
- Whose son is he?
- My friend's.

1618
01:50:59,810 --> 01:51:01,880
He's a very cute child.
Where does he study?

1619
01:51:02,840 --> 01:51:05,320
He'll be going to a
boarding school in Nainital.

1620
01:51:10,770 --> 01:51:13,280
(Crickets chirping)

1621
01:51:21,710 --> 01:51:26,680
(Wood sound)

1622
01:51:48,690 --> 01:51:49,920
(Smashing sound)

1623
01:51:50,280 --> 01:51:51,440
(Dog barks at distance)

1624
01:51:51,470 --> 01:51:52,400
(Whistles)

1625
01:51:58,390 --> 01:51:59,920
(Whistles)

1626
01:52:02,680 --> 01:52:06,170
(Background music)

1627
01:52:30,260 --> 01:52:30,710
DK!

1628
01:52:30,750 --> 01:52:33,390
Rahul is not at home!

1629
01:52:33,950 --> 01:52:36,470
- What!
- I searched everywhere.

1630
01:52:36,650 --> 01:52:38,530
And the front door was open.

1631
01:52:47,600 --> 01:52:48,490
Rahul!

1632
01:52:49,700 --> 01:52:50,510
Rahul!

1633
01:52:51,510 --> 01:52:52,440
Rahul!

1634
01:52:54,240 --> 01:52:56,020
- Rahul!
- Rahul!

1635
01:52:56,080 --> 01:52:57,280
Mummy!

1636
01:52:58,950 --> 01:52:59,820
Rahul!

1637
01:53:00,250 --> 01:53:01,060
Mummy!

1638
01:53:03,950 --> 01:53:04,860
Rahul!

1639
01:53:05,320 --> 01:53:07,480
Mummy! Mummy!

1640
01:53:08,000 --> 01:53:08,920
Dad!

1641
01:53:10,030 --> 01:53:11,950
Stay with the children.
I'll take a look outside.

1642
01:53:16,020 --> 01:53:19,070
What happened, mummy?
Where is Rahul?

1643
01:53:19,110 --> 01:53:19,550
(Gasping)

1644
01:53:19,590 --> 01:53:21,720
- It's nothing.
- Why was Dad shouting his name?

1645
01:53:22,040 --> 01:53:23,460
(Sobbing)

1646
01:53:23,680 --> 01:53:25,290
(Indistinct)

1647
01:53:26,130 --> 01:53:27,510
Mummy.

1648
01:53:27,550 --> 01:53:28,780
It's okay. It's okay.

1649
01:53:29,820 --> 01:53:31,060
Rahul!

1650
01:53:52,190 --> 01:53:54,630
- Watchman, did any child pass by?
- No.

1651
01:53:54,670 --> 01:53:56,590
- Light skinned with blue eyes?
- No, sir.

1652
01:53:57,000 --> 01:54:00,980
(Background music)

1653
01:54:01,570 --> 01:54:02,410
Rahul.

1654
01:54:04,820 --> 01:54:05,830
Rahul.

1655
01:54:16,300 --> 01:54:17,190
What happened?

1656
01:54:17,230 --> 01:54:20,350
He's nowhere to be seen.
Call the police, I'll take the car.

1657
01:54:22,970 --> 01:54:26,370
DK: Wait, Indu...
Don't call the police.

1658
01:54:27,010 --> 01:54:28,840
Give the phone here.
I'll call Suri.

1659
01:54:31,110 --> 01:54:32,940
(Dialing sound)

1660
01:54:41,820 --> 01:54:42,910
Come on!

1661
01:54:43,660 --> 01:54:44,880
Come on!

1662
01:54:48,120 --> 01:54:49,490
MALE: - Hello?
- Come on, come on!

1663
01:54:49,530 --> 01:54:52,090
- Please call Mr. Suri.
MALE: - He's sleeping.

1664
01:54:52,140 --> 01:54:53,950
I know that, but wake him up.

1665
01:54:53,990 --> 01:54:55,790
MALE: - Who's calling?
- I'm DK Malhotra.

1666
01:54:55,810 --> 01:54:58,530
- Call Mr. Suri. It's urgent.
MALE: - But he is sleeping.

1667
01:54:58,570 --> 01:55:00,320
I know he's sleeping!
I say, wake him up!

1668
01:55:02,590 --> 01:55:06,500
Indu, ask Suri to stay ready.
I'll pick him up.

1669
01:55:15,460 --> 01:55:17,040
(Tyre screech)

1670
01:55:18,060 --> 01:55:19,230
Come on, come on, Suri. Hurry up.

1671
01:55:21,150 --> 01:55:22,260
Okay. Let's go.

1672
01:55:41,840 --> 01:55:43,840
- ...DK!
- Rahul!

1673
01:55:44,120 --> 01:55:45,160
There he is!

1674
01:55:45,470 --> 01:55:46,510
Rahul! There.

1675
01:55:47,040 --> 01:55:48,660
Rahul!

1676
01:55:50,150 --> 01:55:52,330
(Foot steps)

1677
01:55:56,370 --> 01:55:59,890
Rahul, where are you running?

1678
01:56:00,530 --> 01:56:01,530
Wait, Rahul!

1679
01:56:09,190 --> 01:56:10,390
Suri, it's not him.

1680
01:56:12,850 --> 01:56:14,020
Damn!

1681
01:56:14,250 --> 01:56:17,570
Where the hell is he?
Where could he have disappeared?

1682
01:56:17,610 --> 01:56:20,130
- Where do I look for him?
- Come on, now!

1683
01:56:20,650 --> 01:56:24,290
What's the use of looking for
him here? It wasn't that boy.

1684
01:56:24,380 --> 01:56:27,500
- What do I do?
- Let's go to the police station.

1685
01:56:28,090 --> 01:56:31,230
So how are you?
How is everything else?

1686
01:56:33,470 --> 01:56:36,590
I'd called you the other day
but you didn't come.

1687
01:56:37,030 --> 01:56:37,880
Yes.

1688
01:56:39,350 --> 01:56:43,240
Well, I don't get the time... Bye.

1689
01:56:45,760 --> 01:56:46,870
(Sighs)

1690
01:56:47,080 --> 01:56:48,910
(Indistinct)

1691
01:56:48,950 --> 01:56:50,510
Could you please hurry?

1692
01:56:50,620 --> 01:56:53,010
(Indistinct)

1693
01:56:54,460 --> 01:56:56,320
Ramu, take him inside.

1694
01:56:57,030 --> 01:56:58,270
Father's name?

1695
01:56:59,460 --> 01:57:00,400
Father's name!

1696
01:57:00,680 --> 01:57:01,550
Come on.

1697
01:57:01,730 --> 01:57:03,730
What will you do with the father's name?

1698
01:57:04,540 --> 01:57:07,620
You have the child's name
and his entire description.

1699
01:57:07,700 --> 01:57:09,580
On finding him, will you
ask him his father's name?

1700
01:57:09,620 --> 01:57:10,680
Father's name?

1701
01:57:13,290 --> 01:57:14,340
(Stammers)

1702
01:57:14,500 --> 01:57:15,430
D.K. Malhotra.

1703
01:57:15,720 --> 01:57:16,570
Louder.

1704
01:57:16,610 --> 01:57:21,010
DK Malhotra! Can't you hear?
DK Malhotra!

1705
01:57:21,390 --> 01:57:22,800
Calm down.

1706
01:57:25,150 --> 01:57:29,900
DK, any news? Did you find him?
Where are you calling from?

1707
01:57:30,130 --> 01:57:33,020
I'm calling from a petrol pump
near the police station.

1708
01:57:33,570 --> 01:57:37,200
We have filed a report at the
police station. But of no avail.

1709
01:57:38,680 --> 01:57:42,410
There's no news of him.
I wonder what's happened to him.

1710
01:57:42,700 --> 01:57:43,940
(Sobbing)

1711
01:57:44,880 --> 01:57:45,850
DK?

1712
01:57:46,930 --> 01:57:47,690
DK.

1713
01:57:49,480 --> 01:57:51,800
Come home.

1714
01:57:52,710 --> 01:57:54,210
It's no use sitting there.

1715
01:57:57,760 --> 01:58:00,490
(Background music)

1716
01:58:00,530 --> 01:58:01,690
What is she saying?

1717
01:58:03,470 --> 01:58:07,950
Excuse me!
Any news of the boy?

1718
01:58:08,200 --> 01:58:09,740
None, yet.

1719
01:58:09,900 --> 01:58:14,060
Of what use is such a big unit?
Can't you find even a child?

1720
01:58:14,090 --> 01:58:15,560
What are you here for?

1721
01:58:16,310 --> 01:58:17,670
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

1722
01:58:18,420 --> 01:58:19,550
You can't even find a...!

1723
01:58:19,660 --> 01:58:20,700
Come on!

1724
01:58:29,360 --> 01:58:31,120
(Door bell)

1725
01:58:38,260 --> 01:58:40,250
We found this boy.
Is he yours?

1726
01:58:43,340 --> 01:58:45,580
We found this letter in his pocket.

1727
01:58:45,620 --> 01:58:49,250
He refused to say where he lives.
This letter had your address.

1728
01:58:50,420 --> 01:58:52,220
Please sign here.

1729
01:58:54,450 --> 01:58:57,930
(Background music)

1730
01:58:58,920 --> 01:58:59,800
Where did you go?

1731
01:59:05,590 --> 01:59:06,950
I asked, where did you go?

1732
01:59:14,980 --> 01:59:17,480
I am asking you something!
Where did you go?

1733
01:59:21,590 --> 01:59:24,990
Aren't you ashamed? You are
a guest at somebody's house!

1734
01:59:25,260 --> 01:59:26,700
We're doing so much for you!

1735
01:59:27,010 --> 01:59:29,780
Instead of being grateful,
this is what you do!

1736
01:59:31,390 --> 01:59:34,130
Now, what's the use of standing
in front of me like a statue?

1737
01:59:34,600 --> 01:59:37,180
You don't even have
the courtesy to apologise!

1738
01:59:38,290 --> 01:59:41,180
I am glad you're leaving!
We'll be rid of you!

1739
01:59:42,900 --> 01:59:45,070
There has been no peace in the
house ever since you've come!

1740
01:59:45,200 --> 01:59:47,560
Do you know how worried
Mini and Winky have been for you?

1741
01:59:47,610 --> 01:59:49,580
Mini hasn't stopped crying!

1742
01:59:49,720 --> 01:59:51,830
And I've been in and around
the house looking for you!

1743
01:59:53,350 --> 01:59:56,880
What would we have done
if you were harmed in any way?

1744
01:59:59,030 --> 02:00:02,350
Does one walk out
at midnight in this city!

1745
02:00:03,010 --> 02:00:04,940
They kidnap small children!

1746
02:00:05,740 --> 02:00:07,690
The entire police force of the city
is in search of you!

1747
02:00:08,700 --> 02:00:10,830
If something were to happen
to you, your father and me...

1748
02:00:13,540 --> 02:00:15,300
I mean, your uncle and I...

1749
02:00:16,630 --> 02:00:18,870
- I know.
- What do you know?

1750
02:00:19,980 --> 02:00:23,770
That he's my Dad.
It is written in the letter.

1751
02:00:27,650 --> 02:00:33,110
(Background music)

1752
02:01:03,640 --> 02:01:04,190
Rahul?

1753
02:01:04,930 --> 02:01:06,050
(Sobbing)

1754
02:01:06,760 --> 02:01:08,070
DK, wait.

1755
02:01:09,740 --> 02:01:10,440
Just a minute.

1756
02:01:21,310 --> 02:01:23,560
- He knows.
- What?

1757
02:01:27,740 --> 02:01:29,080
About your relationship with him.

1758
02:01:31,790 --> 02:01:32,900
How?

1759
02:01:36,360 --> 02:01:37,560
He had this with him.

1760
02:01:41,840 --> 02:01:42,840
Go to him.

1761
02:01:59,220 --> 02:02:08,260
(Background music)

1762
02:02:14,290 --> 02:02:15,840
(Sobbing)

1763
02:02:17,960 --> 02:02:18,770
Rahul...

1764
02:02:33,500 --> 02:02:34,880
Rahul!

1765
02:02:39,340 --> 02:02:40,380
Listen.

1766
02:02:44,380 --> 02:02:47,300
Son, you shouldn't do this.
Where did you go?

1767
02:02:51,740 --> 02:02:55,980
Uncle Suri and I
looked for you everywhere.

1768
02:03:06,700 --> 02:03:07,600
Rahul!

1769
02:03:09,290 --> 02:03:10,270
Are you angry with me?

1770
02:03:20,820 --> 02:03:21,610
What happened?

1771
02:03:24,500 --> 02:03:25,080
Nothing.

1772
02:03:29,660 --> 02:03:30,580
What does he say?

1773
02:03:33,180 --> 02:03:35,390
- Hmm? What?
- Doesn't talk...

1774
02:03:35,430 --> 02:03:36,290
He isn't saying a word.

1775
02:03:38,450 --> 02:03:39,300
I can understand.

1776
02:03:42,890 --> 02:03:44,190
I just can't.

1777
02:03:45,340 --> 02:03:46,190
I can understand.

1778
02:03:51,790 --> 02:03:56,630
Imagine a child who is trying to
trace his father since years...

1779
02:03:56,690 --> 02:03:59,020
...and when he finally
does find him...

1780
02:04:00,120 --> 02:04:01,530
...his father does not accept him.

1781
02:04:03,700 --> 02:04:06,900
He keeps him apart
and sends him far away.

1782
02:04:09,590 --> 02:04:14,690
You can imagine what that
child must be going through.

1783
02:04:17,230 --> 02:04:19,660
Sorry about saying all this.

1784
02:04:19,740 --> 02:04:20,220
Good night.

1785
02:04:20,260 --> 02:04:21,270
(Foot steps)

1786
02:04:22,590 --> 02:04:23,860
Let's go to sleep.

1787
02:04:25,500 --> 02:04:29,620
Carry on. I'll come later.

1788
02:04:46,950 --> 02:04:50,790
Indu, drop the children to school
by taxi in the morning.

1789
02:04:52,160 --> 02:04:53,640
I'll take Rahul to the station.

1790
02:05:02,170 --> 02:05:10,600
"Life, the trials you threw my way
have taught me relationships anew."

1791
02:05:16,320 --> 02:05:24,670
"Life, the trials you threw my way
have taught me relationships anew."

1792
02:05:25,730 --> 02:05:34,010
"The comforts of shade I only found
under the bright scorching sun."

1793
02:05:44,570 --> 02:05:57,420
"I am not angry with you, Life.
Simply baffled."

1794
02:06:09,950 --> 02:06:11,170
Sorry, aunty.

1795
02:06:17,460 --> 02:06:26,090
"Today my eyes have
welled up with tears."

1796
02:06:31,660 --> 02:06:36,500
"Today my eyes have welled up
with tears."

1797
02:06:36,710 --> 02:06:40,550
"Soon they will burst forth, I'm sure."

1798
02:06:41,110 --> 02:06:46,000
"Tomorrow, who knows,
these sore eyes perhaps."

1799
02:06:46,100 --> 02:06:49,590
"Will long for the sight of more."

1800
02:06:50,460 --> 02:06:55,070
"Where have I lost that
lone drop of tears."

1801
02:06:55,520 --> 02:06:59,810
"Which I had tucked away so safely?"

1802
02:06:59,970 --> 02:07:11,530
"I am not angry with you, Life
Simply baffled."

1803
02:07:14,690 --> 02:07:16,400
(Birds chirping)

1804
02:07:17,060 --> 02:07:18,900
- Bye-bye, Rahul.
- Bye-bye.

1805
02:07:24,550 --> 02:07:25,550
Come on, Mini.

1806
02:07:26,890 --> 02:07:29,210
Come, Mini.
We are getting late.

1807
02:07:40,200 --> 02:07:44,580
(Background music)

1808
02:07:51,350 --> 02:07:52,730
(Car door opens)

1809
02:07:53,870 --> 02:07:55,280
(Car door shuts)

1810
02:08:12,450 --> 02:08:14,850
Mummy, why had Rahul run away?

1811
02:08:15,450 --> 02:08:16,140
I don't know.

1812
02:08:19,180 --> 02:08:22,180
Won't he ever return now?

1813
02:08:23,110 --> 02:08:24,270
I don't know.

1814
02:08:24,920 --> 02:08:27,990
- Whom will he stay with?
- With his Dad.

1815
02:08:29,760 --> 02:08:31,440
But he doesn't have a Dad.

1816
02:08:31,990 --> 02:08:36,190
He does. He had drawn his Dad's
picture and showed it to me.

1817
02:08:36,230 --> 02:08:37,290
(Papers sound)

1818
02:08:39,060 --> 02:08:39,780
(Grunts)

1819
02:08:39,860 --> 02:08:42,340
Hey, this is Rahul's sketch book.

1820
02:08:42,400 --> 02:08:44,480
Yes. He gave it to me.

1821
02:08:44,790 --> 02:08:50,110
This is mummy, me, you,
Dad and Brother Rahul.

1822
02:08:50,650 --> 02:08:53,520
This is Brother Rahul and his Dad.

1823
02:08:56,510 --> 02:09:01,340
(Background music)

1824
02:09:05,830 --> 02:09:09,390
Did you strike off Rahul's picture?

1825
02:09:09,420 --> 02:09:10,560
No.

1826
02:09:13,400 --> 02:09:19,080
(Background music)

1827
02:10:00,640 --> 02:10:01,460
Abdul!

1828
02:10:02,660 --> 02:10:05,450
- Where is sir?
- He's taken Rahul to the station.

1829
02:10:05,790 --> 02:10:09,230
(Station announcements)

1830
02:10:15,010 --> 02:10:16,330
Mr. Tiwari! Here.

1831
02:10:16,430 --> 02:10:17,630
DK sir!

1832
02:10:17,680 --> 02:10:19,680
- How are you?
- Let's go, Rahul.

1833
02:10:19,720 --> 02:10:20,920
The train is about to leave.

1834
02:10:21,240 --> 02:10:23,480
- I'll carry it.
- No, allow me.

1835
02:10:24,730 --> 02:10:26,370
- How are you, Rahul?
- This way, Mr. Tiwari.

1836
02:10:27,310 --> 02:10:29,960
(People chattering indistinctly)

1837
02:10:30,030 --> 02:10:32,670
The seat numbers are 55 and 56.

1838
02:10:33,000 --> 02:10:35,480
(People chattering indistinctly)

1839
02:10:40,950 --> 02:10:45,690
(People chattering indistinctly)

1840
02:10:46,690 --> 02:10:50,000
(People chattering indistinctly)

1841
02:10:52,820 --> 02:10:55,050
Come on, Rahul.
The train is about to leave.

1842
02:11:35,360 --> 02:11:38,590
Will you come to meet me?

1843
02:11:42,260 --> 02:11:45,870
Yes, son. I will surely come.
Whenever you say so.

1844
02:11:46,940 --> 02:11:49,620
You won't forget me again, will you?

1845
02:11:49,660 --> 02:11:53,080
No, son. I will never forget you.
...Not this time.

1846
02:11:55,550 --> 02:11:56,950
You won't forget me, will you?

1847
02:11:57,880 --> 02:12:02,280
How can I forget you?
After all, you are my Dad.

1848
02:12:02,660 --> 02:12:07,140
Yes... Yes, son. I'm your Dad.

1849
02:12:10,030 --> 02:12:11,510
I am your Dad.

1850
02:12:16,560 --> 02:12:17,660
Rahul...

1851
02:12:19,680 --> 02:12:21,270
I'm sorry.

1852
02:12:24,390 --> 02:12:25,960
(Sobbing)

1853
02:12:32,920 --> 02:12:35,240
Come on, Rahul, hurry up.
The train is about to leave.

1854
02:12:41,520 --> 02:12:43,280
Write to me once you get there.

1855
02:12:44,220 --> 02:12:46,660
- Mr. Tiwari...
- I've made all the arrangements.

1856
02:12:46,700 --> 02:12:48,290
- Are you sure?
- I've taken care of everything.

1857
02:12:49,590 --> 02:12:52,430
- What about the food?
- I'll arrange it in the train.

1858
02:12:52,470 --> 02:12:54,750
Don't let him have water from outside.

1859
02:12:54,800 --> 02:12:57,240
- Have you kept his water bottle?
- It must be with him.

1860
02:12:57,280 --> 02:12:59,360
- Son, where is your bottle?
- It's in the car.

1861
02:13:00,230 --> 02:13:02,670
- I'll go get it.
- But the train is about to leave!

1862
02:13:02,720 --> 02:13:05,200
Mr. DK, please! The train
is about to leave. Mr. DK!

1863
02:13:12,960 --> 02:13:14,300
Excuse me! Ticket!

1864
02:13:18,600 --> 02:13:19,130
Sorry.

1865
02:13:20,590 --> 02:13:22,350
I'll be back in a moment.
I have to get something.

1866
02:13:22,360 --> 02:13:24,280
- Fine, but where's your ticket?
- I have it.

1867
02:13:24,320 --> 02:13:25,320
But where?

1868
02:13:26,790 --> 02:13:29,390
My child is in the train. I have
to get his bottle. I'll be back.

1869
02:13:29,420 --> 02:13:32,300
- Come this side.
- I repeat, I do have the ticket!

1870
02:13:32,320 --> 02:13:33,760
I say, stand aside!

1871
02:13:38,000 --> 02:13:39,390
(Car horns)

1872
02:13:44,080 --> 02:13:45,190
(Indistinct)

1873
02:13:47,420 --> 02:13:48,740
Whose car is this?

1874
02:13:52,660 --> 02:13:56,200
- Whose car is this?
- That's the person, sir.

1875
02:13:57,340 --> 02:13:58,380
Aye!

1876
02:14:01,840 --> 02:14:05,960
Move your car! Is this how
you park? I can't open my car!

1877
02:14:06,420 --> 02:14:08,700
- Hurry up!
- I'm moving it away.

1878
02:14:08,740 --> 02:14:10,460
The train is about to leave!

1879
02:14:20,160 --> 02:14:24,860
(Background music)

1880
02:15:20,150 --> 02:15:21,200
(Car horns)

1881
02:15:24,560 --> 02:15:26,260
(Traffic noices)

1882
02:15:48,700 --> 02:15:52,240
- Dad, Rahul will stay with us.
- Mummy said so.

1883
02:15:52,820 --> 02:15:55,190
(Indistinct)

1884
02:16:03,450 --> 02:16:07,530
(Indistinct)

1885
02:16:07,570 --> 02:16:12,680
(Indistinct)

1886
02:16:22,620 --> 02:16:23,170
Indu!

1887
02:16:23,250 --> 02:16:25,910
(Indistinct)

1888
02:16:25,950 --> 02:16:27,310
Now, will you keep sitting here...

1889
02:16:29,570 --> 02:16:30,730
...or come home?

1890
02:16:30,920 --> 02:16:35,150
(Children laughing in the background)

1891
02:16:37,370 --> 02:16:39,230
(Car engine starts)

1892
02:16:42,960 --> 02:16:47,200
(Indistinct)

1893
02:16:49,330 --> 02:16:53,300
(Music)

